      • PSCompPOR

        public static CreateHPA PSCompPOR(CreateHPA g1,
                                  CreateHPA g2)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Partially synchronized composition with partial order reduction, automatically sync-ed on shared/common symbols, which should be consistent with com. All states and transitions generated in this function will be reachable.
        Parameters:

      • PSCompMergeERROR

        public static CreateHPA PSCompMergeERROR(CreateHPA gf,
                                         CreateHPA gp,
                                         java.lang.String failedServer)
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Partially synchronized composition, automatically sync-ed on shared/common symbols, which should be consistent with com. All ERROR states will be merged into one during composition. All states and transitions generated in this function will be reachable. Note gfp's final states are defined ALS g1FINAL (suppose p is defeined on g1) and gpFINAL. Also as for situations "g1Final", but either not "pfinal" or not "g1failed", go to ERROR state.
        Pre-condition: no ERROR state in the initial states nor final states; only one ERROR state in gp.
        Parameters:
        gf -
        gp - the two threads to be composed; one is the thread, the other is the property automata.
        failedServer - Specify one session's prefix to clarify on which session is gp defined.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • addFailure

        public void addFailure(CreateHPA g1,
                       CreateHPA g2,
                       java.lang.String failedserver,
                       java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> failedStateIDs,
                       java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> failedInputs,
                       java.util.ArrayList<org.apache.commons.math3.fraction.Fraction> r,
                       java.lang.String failmark,
                       boolean isInterLeaving)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Extend the model with failures. Since there is only one server working after the other failed, 1) if (isInterLeaving == false), the server will first complete the g1 session, then g2 session; 2) if (isInterLeaving == true), the server will first execute g1 until its next input is not T, saying g1 has completed current external input, then execute g2 until its next input is not T, and so on and so forth, interleavingly execute g1 and g2 until they both end; 3)then start a new session on the server that didn't fail. Failure probabilities are defined for specific states [optional] and symbols.
        Parameters:
        g1 -
        g2 - g1 has priority over g2 after failure. But note this g1 and g2 may not be the same order with function PSCompPOR.
        failedserver - a single string denoting the prefix of failed server
        failedStateIDs - size X or 0, specifying states where failure is introduced. It's defined for the specific process which failed.
        failedInputs - size X, specifying symbols on which failure occurs
        r - size X, specifying the probability of the failure is introduced
        failmark - the string to be added to the name of the failed states.
        isInterLeaving - if True, after failure, each session execute an external input interleavingly
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
